programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como visits putting and short game expert Stan Utley in Scottsdale, Arizona. Learn how the putter arch should swing and how to minimize putter face rotation. Plus, Utley demonstrates the best tips for pitch and chip shots.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como spends a day with rising-star coach Lucas Wald and two of his high profile students, Brandel Chamblee, and Eddie Fernandes. Lucas and Brandel demonstrate the adjustments made to Brandel's swing and how modern golf played its part.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como visits PING Headquarters in Phoenix and learns how PING uses technology to make the game simpler for all golfers. Also, meet the "PING Man" and go inside the labs where PING tests clubs and swings.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como spends a day with teaching legend Jim McLean for an in-depth look at his popular swing thoughts and his books. McLean also shares memories from his time with Arnold Palmer, Tiger Woods, and Carl Welty.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.sub-title: Martin Hall - How the Professor Teaches
programme.desc: Chris Como spends a day with "School of Golf" host Martin Hall in his natural habitat; how to visualize the golf swing; how the club path and face affect the swing; how to achieve an ideal impact position; how to find a safe go-to shot.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Multiple-time tour winner Bryson DeChambeau and his coach Chris Como give an inside look of a training session focusing on swing mechanics, the science of golf, and more.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris travels to Jupiter, Florida and learns from Jeff Leishman the importance of the transition and sequence in the swing. Leishman also shares drills that have helped top professionals improve their short game.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.sub-title: How the Trail Arm Works with Justin Bruton
programme.desc: A journey to explore golf's leading teachers, players and influencers.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como visits with Terry Rowles and reveals how he teaches the golf swing based on specific body types. Terry demonstrates how the proper grip and backswing are decided based upon an individual's body measurements.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como visits PGA National Golf Club and shows how his student, Jamie Lovemark, has come back from multiple injuries and swing changes. Jamie also demonstrates workouts that can help prevent future injuries.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como travels the country and learns from the best players and coaches in golf. Como shares the best tips and drills from coaches Jim McLean, Boyd Summerhays, Andrew Getson and many more.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como travels to Miami, FL and learns from Rick Smith, who has worked with Jack Nicklaus, Phil Mickelson, and numerous Major champions. Smith shows Como numerous drills that help his clients produce power and accuracy.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como travels to Frederica Learning Center and sees how Tony Ruggiero trains some of the top young players in the game. 2019 U.S. Amateur Champion Andy Ogletree shares how Tony has him prepping for a tee time in the Masters with Tiger Woods.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.sub-title: Bradley Hughes - Path to Great Golf
programme.desc: Chris Como travels to Holly Tree Country Club and learns how Bradley Hughes uses his playing experience to coach today's top players. Hughes reveals the most effective way to learn the swing and demonstrates a variety of drills.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Bradley Hughes helps players of all skill levels become better ball strikers. Hughes also reveals his key insights that help him coach Brendon Todd, Brandt Snedeker, and other top touring professionals.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: A journey to explore golf's leading teachers, players and influencers.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como travels to Frederica Learning Center and sees how Tony Ruggiero trains some of the top young players in the game; 2019 U.S. Amateur Champion Andy Ogletree shares how Tony has him prepping for a tee time in the Masters with Tiger Woods.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.desc: Chris Como and Jon Tattersall head to the race track and show how driving high-performance cars is similar to a well-tuned golf swing. Tattersall puts those concepts into action on the range with drills on how to become a better ball striker.

programme.title: Swing Expedition With Chris Como
programme.sub-title: Deep Dive - Physics with Sasho MacKenzie
programme.desc: A journey to explore golf's leading teachers, players and influencers.

programme.sub-title: Deep Dive - Brandel Chamblee & Lucas Wald

programme.title: Big Break: Where Are They Now?
programme.desc: We catch up with former Big Break competitors Isaac Sanchez and Chad Pfeifer.Sanchez, who goes by the nickname "Sasquatch," is in actuality a gentle giant. But that didn't stop the competitor in him from creating some mythical moments.

programme.title: Big Break: Where Are They Now?
programme.sub-title: Mallory Blackwelder, Julien Trudeau & Robbie Biershenk
programme.desc: A look at where the aspiring golfers from "The Big Break" are now.

programme.title: Big Break: Where Are They Now?
programme.desc: A look at where the aspiring golfers from "The Big Break" are now.

programme.title: Big Break: Where Are They Now?
programme.sub-title: Don Donatello & Stefanie Kenoyer; Al Del Greco
programme.desc: Don Donatello earned notoriety for his outbursts and antics, but quickly became heralded as a gritty competitor. Appearances on Big Break IV U.S. vs. Europe and Big Break Reunion solidified Donatello as legendary.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy and Piers want to get the most out of the driver. They demonstrate what the pros look like at impact and share what to do to get into that position.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy Proudman and Piers Ward cover all things long game from fairway metals to hybrids and even how to master the dreaded long irons. They also teach how finding the low point in the swing helps create consistent strikes.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy Proudman and Piers Ward explain the big three in iron play: how to control distance, accuracy, and trajectory on shots. They also show a footwork drill to help ball striking and what to do to work the ball into those tucked pins.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy Proudman and Piers Ward explain how to dial in distances with short irons and how to hit them on line every time; they also explain the bounce angle and how to choose the right amount.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy and Piers show how to play a variety of shots around the green, including the high spinning chip, low runner, and many more. They also explain the importance of focusing on a landing zone when hitting greenside shots.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
programme.desc: Andy and Piers explain the necessary fundamentals to hit effective greenside and fairway bunker shots. They also explain how to hit it close from one of the most feared shots in the game, the 30-40-yard bunker shot.

programme.title: Me and My Golf
